      solution: "As we need to find the most general solution for two different trigonometric equations. tan θ θ = -1 …..........(i) and cos θ θ = 1 2 √ 1 2 ….........(ii) Most general value of θ θ is the common solution of both equation (i) and (ii). Let S 1 represents the solution set of equation (i) and S 2 be the solution set equation (ii). Let S represents the set of most general value of θ θ ∴ ∴ S = S 1 ∩ ∩ S 2 We know that, solution of tan x = tan α is given by: x = n π + α ∀ n ∈ Z n π + α ∀ n ∈ Z and solution of cos x = cos α α is given by: x = 2 m π ± a ∀ m ∈ Z 2 m π ± a ∀ m ∈ Z From equation (i), we have: tan θ θ = -1 ⇒ tan θ θ = tan (- π 4 π 4 ) ∴ ∴ θ = n π + ( - π 4 ) = ( n π - π 4 ) ∀ n ∈ Z θ = n π + ( - π 4 ) = ( n π - π 4 ) ∀ n ∈ Z ….....(iii) From equation (ii) we have: cos θ θ = 1 2 √ 1 2 ⇒ cos θ θ = cos π 4 π 4 ⇒ θ θ = 2 m π ± π 4 ∀ m ∈ Z 2 m π ± π 4 ∀ m ∈ Z ......…(iv) From equation (iii) we can infer that, solution lies either in 2 nd quadrant (when n is odd) and 4 th quadrant (when n is even) From equation (iii) we can infer that, solution lies either in 1 st or 2 nd quadrant irrespective of value of m. ∴ ∴ region of common solution is 4 th quadrant and n is even in that case. ∴ ∴ common solution is given by: θ θ = 2 m π - π 4 ∀ m ∈ Z 2 m π - π 4 ∀ m ∈ Z The above solution is the most general solution for the given two equations i.e, tan θ θ = -1 and cos θ θ = 1 2 √ 1 2",
